rComments: His classes are a lot of fun and I always looked forward to him. His lectures are detailed and straight forward.
You have to read the textbook and attend class if you want to do well but he is a hilarious prof and he cares about teaching his students to fully understand the material - not just memorize it.

His lectures are quite confusing so far. Not sure where to start studying, let alone how or what. He's a little disorganized and doesn't seem to know where to take the class in the material. Lots of quotes in the slides. With that said, he is one of the most hilarious profs I've ever had. Really relates with students!

He's a great professor. Did not go one class without laughing really hard at his stories. He is articulate and is always willing to help out if you have any questions. His examples are relevant and he knows what he is talking about, he's also very willing to clarify if asked. Just do your readings and attend class, it's worth it. Super cool guy.

I'll admit, his midterm was pretty difficult. But even then, his class was one of my favourites this year! He is so funny and makes me actually want to go to my 8:30 Monday morning class! He's always available for questions!! If you have the option to take him, DO IT!

David was a funny guy overall, but his midterm was pretty difficult. His grading structure also wasn't helpful and he wouldn't give you much feedback unless you spoke to him during his office hours. His lectures are fun and informative, but it can be a chore to write everything on his slides while also trying to understand what he's saying.

Loved him! He is hilarious, always there for students, always answers emails and wants you to succeed. He is a little bit confusing at time in his lectures, however, if you read the textbook you'll do great. Assignments are fun to do and there are a lot so it gives a better chance at a better grade.

Didn't go to one lecture without dying of laughter. Hilarious guy. Super nice, quirky too; a bit of a comic-geek type of guy. Very picky about proper englishgrammar etc. and refuses to post the slides online. Difficult to study off of notes you take in his class, as you don't have time to copy slides AND what he says. Pretty enjoyable class,though
